wikipedia_page.main: Stuart Johnston Symington, born at Bexhill-on-Sea, Sussex, on 16 September 1926 and died at Hereford on 11 December 2009, played first-class cricket for Leicestershire as an amateur in 1948 and 1949. He was captain of the Leicestershire side in 1949. After little more than a year in full-time cricket, he resumed a career in the Army.
